---
description: Animation and motion standards for all UI surfaces
globs:
  - "ui/src/**"
  - "apps/**"
  - "website/src/**"
---

- Use `var(--sc-duration-fast)`, `var(--sc-duration-normal)`, `var(--sc-duration-slow)` — never hardcode `100ms`, `200ms`, `0.2s`, etc.
- Use `var(--sc-ease-out)`, `var(--sc-ease-in-out)` — never hardcode `cubic-bezier(...)` or `ease`
- Use spring tokens: `--sc-spring-micro` for button/toggle, `--sc-spring-standard` for panels, `--sc-spring-expressive` for page transitions, `--sc-spring-dramatic` for hero reveals
- Native iOS: use `SCTokens.springMicro`, `SCTokens.springStandard`, `SCTokens.springExpressive`, `SCTokens.springDramatic`
- Every animation/transition must work with `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce`
- Keyframe names: `sc-` prefix (e.g. `sc-fade-in`, `sc-slide-up`)
- Never use `setTimeout` for animation timing — use CSS transitions or `requestAnimationFrame`
- Animate only compositor properties: `transform`, `opacity`, `filter` — never animate `width`, `height`, `top`, `left`, `margin`, `padding` (causes layout thrashing)
- For layout changes, use `transform: translateX/Y/scale()` instead of position/size properties
- Glass choreography: use `.sc-glass-enter` / `.sc-glass-exit` classes for blur/saturation reveal animations
- Glass state transitions: all glass classes have `backdrop-filter` in their CSS transition property — blur/saturation animate between states
- Glass choreography tokens: `--sc-glass-choreography-enter-duration` (350ms), `--sc-glass-choreography-exit-duration` (200ms), `--sc-glass-choreography-state-duration` (200ms)
- Glass choreography easing: `--sc-glass-choreography-enter-easing` (M3 emphasize), `--sc-glass-choreography-state-easing` (M3 emphasize)
- `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce` disables all glass choreography animations
- `prefers-reduced-transparency: reduce` replaces glass with solid `--sc-bg-surface` backgrounds
